      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box\">\n<blockquote>Following Google's corporate restructuring under the conglomerate Alphabet Inc. in October 2015, Alphabet took \"Do the right thing\" as its motto, also forming the opening of its corporate code of conduct.[5][6][7][1][8] The original motto was retained in Google's code of conduct, now a subsidiary of Alphabet. Between 21 April and 4 May 2018, the motto was removed from the code of conduct's preface and retained in its last sentence.[9]</blockquote><br/>\n<br/>\nGoogle的不作恶在当年有特殊意义，后来经过管理层各种变动，早就不再是对外宣传的重点了。现在只是对内培训的一部分。\t\t</div>",
